--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PER-DIRECTORY LICENSING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Licensing is assigned at the directory level. The authoritative mapping
is maintained in:

  https://github.com/pointsav/factory-release-engineering/blob/main/mapping/repo-license-map.yaml

Directories under AGPL-3.0-or-later:

  os-console/        — platform console
  os-privategit/     — private git module
  os-totebox/        — core platform
  os-workplace/      — workplace module
  service-*/         — all platform services
  system-*/          — all platform systems
  tool-*/            — all platform tools
  moonshot-*/        — experimental and speculative work
  app-console-*/     — applications extending os-console
  app-privategit-*/  — applications extending os-privategit
  app-totebox-*/     — applications extending os-totebox
  app-workplace-*/   — applications extending os-workplace
  foundry-nodeclass/ — workspace node classification library
  scripts/           — workspace build and automation scripts
  slm/               — language model module configuration
  docs/              — internal technical documentation

Directories under FSL-1.1-ALv2 (Functional Source License 1.1 with
Apache-2.0 future license):

  os-infrastructure/   — infrastructure module
  os-interface/        — interface module (renames to os-orchestration)
  os-mediakit/         — media kit module
  os-network-admin/    — network administration module
  app-mediakit-*/      — applications extending os-mediakit
  app-network-*/       — applications extending os-network-admin
  templates/           — HTML/CSS shell templates for app-mediakit surfaces

Directories carrying upstream third-party licenses:

  vendor-virtio/     — virtio driver stubs; see vendor-virtio/README.md for SPDX
  vendor-wireguard/  — WireGuard tooling; see vendor-wireguard/README.md for SPDX

The full AGPL-3.0-or-later text is available at:
  https://github.com/pointsav/factory-release-engineering/blob/main/licenses/AGPL-3.0.txt

The full FSL-1.1-ALv2 text is available at:
  https://github.com/pointsav/factory-release-engineering/blob/main/licenses/FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0.txt

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LOCAL-ONLY DIRECTORIES (not tracked in this repository)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following directories exist on operator machines but are gitignored and
never committed to this repository:

  app-infrastructure-*/  — per-deployment infrastructure instances
  vendor-azure-auth/     — Microsoft Azure authentication libraries
  vendor-gpu-drivers/    — GPU driver packages
  vendor-linux-systemd/  — systemd library bindings
  vendor-microsoft-graph/— Microsoft Graph SDK
  vendor-phi3-mini/      — Phi-3 Mini model weights
  vendor-sel4-kernel/    — seL4 microkernel source
  vendor-slm-engine/     — local language model engine
  discovery-queue/       — operator-local transaction queue

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
COMMERCIAL ALTERNATIVE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Customers who cannot accept the terms of AGPLv3 or who require use of
FSL-licensed code before its Delayed Open Source Publication window
expires may obtain a PointSav Commercial License. Contact
corporate.secretary@woodfinegroup.com for details.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
POLICIES AND GOVERNANCE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Repository-wide policies apply regardless of per-directory licensing:

  - CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md  — Contributor Covenant 2.1
  - CONTRIBUTING.md     — contribution workflow and CLA requirements
  - SECURITY.md         — vulnerability disclosure policy
  - TRADEMARK.md        — trademark and trade-dress policy

All of these are propagated from factory-release-engineering and should
not be edited in this repository. Propose changes upstream.

